Phoo is a Qt6 encrypted messenger.

It works on all desktop platforms, and Android.
Dwyco distributes the Android version basically as a companion app for CDC-X.
(NOTE: it works on iOS too, but due to lack of Apple hardware, I can't test it currently. And it needs some work to do background message sends and syncing.)

Current requirements:
* Qt 6.8+
* For Linux: Ubuntu 22.04+
* To build for android, you'll need an android sdk/ndk installation. QtCreator can usually do this ok. Note that the cmake build files assume you are using Qt installed from the Qt online installer.

(WARNING: Tue Mar  3 11:50:17 AM MST 2026, working on moving from ndk-build to cmake for builds. Things are likely to be broken for android builds)
